            {
                "id": 25,
                "name": "Stairs and Hallway",
                "description": "Several ways to get between the ground floor and the one above. Surrounding the area on the upstairs floor is a railed walkway, with doors out to other rooms. To the west is the top of the stairs and a slide, both going down to the east. A glass elevator is on the southeast corner of the area just outside the bedroom, while a built-in ladder, pole, and rope are next to each other in the northeast corner.\r\n\r\nAlso to the east is a large upstairs window, lighting the area.\r\n\r\nMaster bedroom (upstairs) and rec room (ground floor) are south of here, while the downstairs hallway is north.",
                "attribs": [],
                "abilities": [],
                "dimensions": null,
